  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Sports Coach & Operations",
  "description": "<p>Join Umeus Group — Home of Singapore’s Largest Pickleball Community</p><p>Umeus is expanding. As Singapore’s leading lifestyle ecosystem and home to the country’s biggest pickleball club, we are looking for passionate, high-calibre coaches to join our team.</p><p>If you’re an ex-high-level athlete, an experienced instructor, or a certified coach with a great personality and deep love for racquet sports — we want you.<br /></p><p><strong>What You’ll Be Part Of</strong></p><p>Umeus Group is a multi-brand sports, lifestyle and wellness organisation. Our coaches are known for being energetic, engaging, and delivering world-class experiences every single session. We are now growing our coaching team across tennis, pickleball, and padel.<br /></p><p><strong>Role: Sports Coach (Full-Time)</strong><br /></p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><p>Coach group classes, private lessons, and corporate programs (tennis, pickleball, or padel)<br />Deliver high-quality, structured, fun, and engaging sessions<br />Assist with program development, training curriculum, and events<br />Assist with operational tasks as per business needs<br />Provide clear guidance and mentorship to students of all ages and levels<br />Uphold Umeus Group coaching standards and culture<br />Represent our brand on-court with professionalism, positivity, and leadership<br />Support community events, pop-ups, and club initiatives<br /><br />Who We’re Looking For :<br />Former competitive athlete AND/OR experienced/certified coach<br />Strong technical foundation in at least one racquet sport<br />Energetic, friendly, reliable, and great with people<br />Able to deliver engaging, structured, and safe coaching sessions<br />Passionate about continuous learning and development<br />Team-player with a positive attitude<br />Comfortable communicating in English<br />Bonus: Certified under PPR, PTR, ITF, GPTCA, Padel Federation, etc.<br /></p><p><strong>Career Growth & Opportunities</strong></p><ul><li>Stable full-time salary</li><li>Long-term career path within Umeus Group (multi-brand ecosystem)</li><li>Coaching development with Asia's top players and coaches</li><li>Potential to lead programs, manage locations.<br /></li></ul><p><strong>Why Join Us</strong></p><ul><li>Be part of a fast-growing sports & lifestyle ecosystem</li><li>A fun, professional, energetic team culture</li><li>Strong community and premium clientele</li></ul>",
